race.comment: TRINITY'S D'ORO (8) broke her Maiden here last start over 1628m in a return to form. Finished hard and is nicely placed to double the win tally. ZE BEE NINE (3) is busting to win and there's been nothing in it his last three. Led the latest at Kilmore over 1460m and has a handy 2kg claim. He's capable of taking a sit and should see out the extra metres. TIGHT GRIP (5) was beaten 2.5 lengths in a 1600m contest at Cranbourne nine days ago. Defied the market but had been good at Mornington prior, and has to be considered. CRYPTIC CLUE (4) also defied a lack of market support scoring by 3L lengths over this distance at Bairnsdale in a 56. Can't be ruled out based on that effort. BOOKMAN (1) went close at Warrnambool and maps for a soft run. It's been a long time between drinks for him.
